  <description type="morphology">Plants with numerous stems, slender, succulent. Stems prostrate to decumbent, much-branched, 5–15(–21) cm × 0.5–2.5 mm, internodes of main stem 5–30 mm. Leaves: main stem leaves evenly spaced, of similar size on all stems; blade elliptic or ovate to obovate, 4–20(–30) × 3–9(–18) mm, apex acute to apiculate. Pedicels 3–10(–15) mm. Flowers: sepals ovate, 3.5–6 mm, apex apiculate. Capsules 7–10 × 8–12 mm, chartaceous. Seeds reddish to yellowish brown, 2–4 mm, glossy. 2n = 66, 68, 70 (Asia).</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering summer.</description>
